<b>The 18th Annual Publius Fellows Program</b><br>
<font size=3 FACE="Times New Roman">
The Publius Fellows Program is an intensive four-week summer course in political philosophy designed for college seniors and graduate students who are interested in writing for the public prints. Now in its eighteenth year, the Publius Fellows Program is dedicated to preserving the tradition of American political writing. It aims to foster constructive commentary on the important issues of today, informed and moderated by an understanding of the philosophical and historical roots of American democracy. 
