<META name="description" content="Issues `96 is intended as a handbook for conservative candidates of all parties seeking national office. It is broken down into sections, one dealing with domestic issues likely to be part of the debate, and the other dealing with foreign policy and defense issues."> 

<META name="keywords" content="Heritage, conservative, research, Issues 96, Issues '96, domestic, foreign, economic, national security, national defense, budget, tax, taxes, regulation, environment,  labor, employment, wages, social, values, welfare, crime, education, health care, health reform, health, immigration, term limits, congressional reform, affirmative action, race preferences, sex-based preferences, federalism, defense, isolationism, defending america, missile defense, trade, development, public opinion, Issues 1996">
