<title>The Flat Tax Offer - Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<center><h1>RECEIVE YOUR COPY OF<br>
 <i>THE FLAT TAX</i> -- FREE!</h1></center>
<blockquote><img src="flattax.gif" width=300 height=535 align=left hspace=15>
<h2>THE FLAT TAX</h2><br>
<h4><I>Honest Tax Reform that</I>:</h4><p>
<table border=0><tr valign="top">
<td><img src="star.gif" width=20 height=18 hspace=10 align=top></td><td><h3>Cuts Taxes, <I>Especially<br> for Families</I></h3></td>
</tr><tr valign="top">
<td><img src="star.gif" width=20 height=18 hspace=10 align=top></td><td><h3>Reduces Power of<br> Special Interests</h3></td>
</tr><tr valign="top">
<td><img src="star.gif" width=20 height=18 hspace=10 align=top></td><td><h3>Curbs IRS Abuses</h3></td>
</tr><tr valign="top">
<td>
<img src="star.gif" width=20 height=18 hspace=10 align=top></td><td><h3>Ignites Our Economy <br>and Creates New Jobs</h3></td>
</tr><tr valign="top">
<td><img src="star.gif" width=20 height=18 hspace=10 align=top></td><td><h3>Restores Honesty to<br> Government</h3></td>
</tr></table>
<p>
<table border=0 align=right width="340">
<tr valign="top">
<td><p>
<sup>"</sup><font size="+1">T</font><font size="-1">he most accessible guide to the flat tax is probably the one written by Daniel Mitchell of The Heritage Foundation</font>." <br>
<b><i>The Wall Street Journal</i></b>, <font size="-1">April 15, 1996</font>

<p>

<sup>"</sup><font size="+1">M</font><font size="-1">itchell marvelously demonstrates how the flat tax will rip away the principal source of political pollution in Washington and replace this anti-growth, anti-family, legalized cesspool of corruption with a new system that will return power and opportunity to the American people."</font> <b><I>Steve Forbes</I></b>
<p>
<sup>"</sup><font size="+1">S</font><font size="-1">crapping our complex tax system for a flat tax is one of the most significant steps we can take to restore America's economic growth. Dan Mitchell's new book shows why this tax reform needs to be at the top of the action list for next year's Congress."</font> <b><I>Connie Mack, United States Senator</I></b>
</td></tr></table>
<p>&#160;
<p>&#160;
<p>&#160;
<p>&#160;


